  "status": "polynomial-layout-exact-and-approximate-density-one-routes-closed-partial-route-open",
  "summary": "Proved exact fiber Schmidt spectra plus density-one simultaneous exact and 99-percent-fidelity exponential-rank bounds for polynomial layout dictionaries across 5 scaling rows. Finite Schmidt rows=10; polynomial state preparations/solvers=0/0.",
  "theorem": {
    "approximate_polynomial_bond_density_one_route_ruled_out": true,
    "approximate_rank_bound": "With Markov factor a, purity<=4a*M*B_L*B_R/mu_full^2 except with probability <=1/a+4/mu_full; Schmidt mass eta requires rank at least eta^2/purity",
    "constant_fraction_exponential_rank_proved": true,
    "constant_probability_rank_bound": "If c=p_L*p_R and gamma<c, Pr[rank>=gamma*M] >= (c-gamma)/(1-gamma); choose gamma=c/2",
    "exact_polynomial_bond_density_one_route_ruled_out": true,
    "exact_rank": "rank(psi_t)=|supp(L) intersect (t-supp(R))|",
    "exact_schmidt_decomposition_proved": true,
    "exact_spectrum": "p_r=L_r*R_(t-r)/C_t for every residue with both factors nonzero, where C_t=sum_r L_r R_(t-r)",
    "expected_rank_fraction_bound": "E[rank]/M >= p_L*p_R for independent left and right labels",
    "expected_squared_block_weight_bound": "For Q=sum_r (L_r R_(t-r))^2, E[Q] <= M*B_L*B_R with B_d=(1+mu_d)^2+mu_d",
    "full_fiber_concentration_bound": "For C_t=sum_r L_r R_(t-r), Pr[C_t<mu_full/2] <= 4/mu_full by pairwise-independence variance",
    "polynomial_layout_dictionary_density_one_route_ruled_out": true,
    "polynomial_layout_family_bound": "For at most n^d instance-independent balanced cuts, choose Markov factor a=n^(d+2). A union bound gives simultaneous rank 2^(q-O(log n)) with failure at most n^-2+4/mu_full.",
    "proof": "Grouping basis rows and columns by subset-sum residue makes the coefficient matrix a direct sum of rank-one all-ones blocks, proving the spectrum. Distinct nonempty Boolean subset indicators have a 2x2 minor of determinant +/-1, so their sums are pairwise independent over Z_(2^q). Paley-Zygmund bounds each side's support; independence of the two label halves and a bounded-variable tail argument give the exact-rank certificate. The same pairwise independence bounds side second moments and concentrates the full fiber count; Markov plus Cauchy-Schwarz then gives the approximate-rank certificate.",
    "scope_exclusions": [
      "general polynomial-size quantum circuits, which can create volume-law entanglement",
      "partial solvers succeeding on an inverse-polynomial subset of easier random instances",
      "approximate preparation concentrated on a selected inverse-polynomial easy-instance subset",
      "coordinate orderings outside the declared fixed polynomial balanced-layout dictionary",
      "instance-adaptive orderings selected from more than a fixed polynomial layout dictionary",
      "time lower bounds inferred only from Schmidt rank"
    ],
    "side_support_probability_bound": "Pr[N_r>0] >= mu/(mu+1-1/M), mu=(2^d-1)/M, by pairwise independence and Paley-Zygmund",
